The Transition Monitoring Group (TMG), a foremost independent civil society election observation organization in Nigeria has embarked on a nationwide voter education awareness rally and sensitization campaign.  The TMG voter education awareness rally and sensitization campaign, which was held on Friday, is coming ahead of the March 18th Governorship and State Assembly elections in the country. The voter education awareness rally and sensitization campaign touched major metropolis comprising of mall, major motor parks and motor garage, business areas, ultra-modern markets and corporate offices saturated areas in Anambra, Imo, Nasarawa, Niger, other states of the federation.  See photos below